# GAN-based Image Steganography

PyTorch implementation of GAN-based image steganography inspired by the HiDDeN paper.

## Project Structure

```
MajorP/
├── data/                   # Data directory
│   ├── raw/               # Raw datasets
│   ├── processed/         # Processed datasets
│   └── outputs/           # Generated outputs
├── src/                   # Source code
│   ├── models/            # Model architectures
│   ├── data/              # Data loading and preprocessing
│   ├── losses/            # Loss functions
│   ├── utils/             # Utility functions
│   └── training/          # Training logic
├── configs/               # Configuration files
├── notebooks/             # Jupyter notebooks for experiments
├── scripts/               # Training and evaluation scripts
├── tests/                 # Unit tests
└── checkpoints/           # Model checkpoints
```

## Setup

```bash
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

## Features

- Modular architecture for CNN baseline and GAN extension
- Configurable training pipeline
- Support for multiple datasets
- Comprehensive evaluation metrics

## References

- HiDDeN: Hiding Data With Deep Networks (Zhu et al., 2018)
